---
description: Rules for reporting and BI-ready outputs
alwaysApply: false
---

For reporting and BI tasks:

Focus:
- Business clarity over technical detail
- Executive-friendly language
- Clear KPIs and consistent naming

Always:
- Separate descriptive insights from model-based insights
- Avoid overstating causality
- Mention assumptions and limitations
- Save BI-ready tables in `reports/tables/`
- Save figures in `reports/figures/`

Good outputs include:
- churn rate summary
- segment-level churn analysis
- model metric summary
- high-risk customer export
- executive summary